[DhtmlXQ_comment33]And red would still hold on to a slight lead in the game.||Thus far, all of the major pieces for both sides are intact and both have decent formations.||The real fight in this variation is in the midgame and endgame which requires skills in this stages. The outcome would still take some time before it can be decided.||In summary:||red's rapid R2+6 with left proper horse and left ranked chariot variation has developed into an important and huge variation of the central cannon when faced with the screen horse defense with double headed snake pawn formation.||It is impossible to introduce or point out the intricacies with just a few boards. The best way the beginner can learn is through actual play and practice so that one could learn the intricacies more. There are many tactics to be used also in this opening. 　[/DhtmlXQ_comment33]
